	<Sentence>
		<value>BiPAP is useful for children and adults who have:  - Airways that collapse while sleeping, making it hard to breathe freely  - Decreased air exchange in the lung  - Muscle weakness that makes it difficult to breathe, due to conditions such as muscular dystrophy   CPAP or BiPAP may also be used by people who have:  - Respiratory failure  - Central sleep apnea  - COPD  - Heart failure   HOW CPAP WORKS  When using CPAP:  - You wear a mask over your nose or nose and mouth while you sleep.</value>
